metadata.name: It just doesn't mean
metadata.description:
Tim Buckley is taking the recruitment process very seriously.



The talented players on full scholarships are recruited by the head coach and have nothing to do with him.



The main strength of the team is these talented players.



It just doesn't mean the other players aren't important.



12 players on a team. How many full scholarship talents are there?



They represent the bulk of the team, but the remaining role players are also important.



Marquette doesn't have the luxury of a top school like Duke or North Carolina.



These teams are filled with talented high school students, even five-star high school students!
